r:black;font-weight:normal;\"><br /></span></strong></span></div><div><span style=\"color:red;\"><strong><span style=\"color:black;font-weight:normal;\">Face-to-face class&nbsp;</span></strong></span><span style=\"color:red;\"><strong><span style=\"color:black;font-weight:normal;\">《90minutes》</span></strong></span></div></div><div><br /></div><div>Project 2 preparation</div>", "Project Preparation (2 Hours)"], "第15回": ["<div><div><span style=\"color:red;\"><strong><span style=\"color:black;font-weight:normal;\">【Core Week 12】</span></strong></span></div><div><span style=\"color:red;\"><strong><span style=\"color:black;font-weight:normal;\"><br /></span></strong></span></div><div><span style=\"color:red;\"><strong><span style=\"color:black;font-weight:normal;\">Face-to-face class&nbsp;</span></strong></span><span style=\"color:red;\"><strong><span style=\"color:black;font-weight:normal;\">《90minutes》</span></strong></span></div></div><div><br /></div><div>Project 2 assignment</div>", "Course Reflections (2 Hours)"], "授業外学習2": "Students will learn research skills, advanced communication skills teamwork skills and about social responsibility and research ethics in this course. They will then be required to actively use these skills to do research on a topic chosen by the teacher or the class. They will work with class members to present and give feedback as they work on their projects to improve them and produce a final report and present it to a larger audience.<br /><br />Open to KGU students, first year and above. Students must be self-directed, hard-working with good communication skills and to be willing to work closely with other students."}, "評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["Course materials will be provided by the instructor and sourced by students."], "参考文献・資料/Reference books0": ["English dictionary (paper or electronic) is highly recommended."], "学位授与の方針との関連Relationship to Diploma Policy0": ["各授業科目は、各学部・研究科の定めるディプロマ・ポリシー（DP）・カリキュラム・ポリシー（CP）に基づき、カリキュラム上に配置されています。\nDP・CPを意識して本授業科目の学修を進めることで、各学部・研究科の期待する能力が養成されます。\n各学部・研究科のDP、CPや教育課程表（授業科目一覧等）は、下記リンクこちらに掲載していますので学修計画の参考にしてください。\nhttps://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/reference?typeCd=0&amp;cabinetId=557&amp;directLink=1\n※kwicへのリンクとなります（在学生のみ閲覧可）"], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["その他／Others (99)", "100 %", "See below for grading criteria."], "成績評価Grading2": ["備考　Note 30% Active Participation in Classroom Activities30% Research Activity (Individual and Group)20% Discussion and Presentation Projects20% Digital PortfolioThere is no final examination(定期試験).Deduction from the final grade of 2 points for each unexcused absence and 1 point for late attendance to class.Remember attendance alone will not be sufficient to pass the course. Students MUST actively contribute to class discussions.Late submissions of homework, assignments, projects will NOT be accepted.出席、遅刻の制度については以下URL先をご確認ください。/ Please refer to the following URL for details regarding the attendance and tardiness policy.https://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/area/detail?areaId=7144&amp;directLink=1"], "備考Note0": ["この授業を履修するには、事前にレベル認定の申請が必要です。詳細は下記URL（kwicのキャビネット）の「履修手続」を確認してください。"], "備考Note1": ["英語インテンシブ・プログラム　履修について"], "備考Note2": ["2026年03月11日 14時27分46秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "春学期／Spring", "水曜３時限／Wednesday 3", "春学期／Spring", "Ｇ－２０６"]}, "campas": 0, "name": "【300】Project-based Seminar in English（Japan Studies）　１／Project-based Seminar in English(Japan Studies)", "管理部署": 20, "単位数": 2, "担当者": "ヒギンズ　Ｒ．Ｍ．（HIGGINS ROBERT MICHAEL） ", "履修基準年度": "１年", "履修登録方法": "申込制(他条件あり)", "開講期": 1, "時限1": 16, "評価1": 6, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\n30% Active Participation in Classroom Activities\n30% Research Activity (Individual and Group)\n20% Discussion and Presentation Projects\n20% Digital Portfolio\n\n\nThere is no final examination(定期試験).\n\nDeduction from the final grade of 2 points for each unexcused absence and 1 point for late attendance to class.\n\nRemember attendance alone will not be sufficient to pass the course. Students MUST actively contribute to class discussions.\n\nLate submissions of homework, assignments, projects will NOT be accepted.\n\n出席、遅刻の制度については以下URL先をご確認ください。/ Please refer to the following URL for details regarding the attendance and tardiness policy.\nhttps://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/area/detail?areaId=7144&directLink=1"}